radiographic_examinations.findings: Single active fetus, right lateral complete placenta previa, large echolucencies in the placenta, loss of the myometrial echolucent stripe near the bladder, increased venous structures and flow in the anterior lower uterine segment, features suggestive of placenta accreta.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up ultrasound at 27 weeks confirmed complete placenta previa and all previously noted sonographic signs of placenta accreta.
